{
    "action": "sale_or_purchase",  // Action type: "sale" for sale, "purchase" for restocking
    "shop_id": "shop-uuid",  // Shop ID
    "product_id": "product-uuid",  // Product ID
    "quantity": 1,  // Default is 1; user can adjust for sales or purchase
    "price": 100.0,  // For purchase actions, this is the price at which the product was bought
    "is_discounted": false,  // Whether this sale has a discount (for sale actions)
    "discount_amount": 0.0,  // If is_discounted is true, specify the discount amount
    "user_action": "confirm",  // User action: "confirm" to confirm action, or "cancel" to abort
    "timestamp": "2025-03-27T14:00:00Z"  // Timestamp of the transaction
  }
  
  supplier to track most sold product and highest profit product
  products update stock and status
  supplierPriceHistory to check price of supplier
  sales to add quantity of product with customer id if available

  for debt, after scanning qrcodes you need to enter some infos manually 
  and this can consume time so cash customers are served first.

  returns gives manual insertion of data.

  cash sales goes to sales table (product_id, quantity, shopId, saleType, customerId)
  purchases goes to expenses
  debt sales goes to debt and logic beside insertion

  manual tracking of asked products